      "writtenOn": "2020-11-23T14:20:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think there\u0027s two distinct kinds of things going on in there,\n   \n   1) recognizing that bilerp mechanically becomes nearest neighbor when the sample points are in just the right spots\n   2) some sort of Chrome bug fix for edges I don\u0027t really understand (Florin?)\n\nI\u0027ve got no problem applying 1) any time it\u0027s legal... it\u0027s free math.  2) I don\u0027t understand enough to have an opinion on.  I would like to know if there\u0027s somewhere higher-level that logic can live... it\u0027s another why-do-this-if-Ganesh-doesn\u0027t question.",
      "revId": "e39c7c06331562186d6a57fcb15d15681ec340cb",
